# Walkthrough: Customer Support Chatbot Guardrails

## What Was Built

A comprehensive guardrails implementation in [01_guardrails.py](file:///Users/shardulmac/Documents/Projects/Projects/LangChain/AdvancedUsecases/Guardrails/01_guardrails.py) covering **every guardrail type** from the [LangChain documentation](file:///Users/shardulmac/Documents/Projects/Projects/LangChain/AdvancedUsecases/Guardrails/LangChain_guardrails_documentation.md), applied to a Customer Support Chatbot.

---

## LLM Migration: Google Gemini Integration

The system has been successfully migrated from OpenAI to **Google Gemini**.

- **Model**: `models/gemini-flash-latest` (Gemini 1.5 Flash)
- **Integration Layer**: `langchain-google-genai`
- **Technical Fixes**:
  - **Content Normalization**: Added `get_content_as_string` helper to handle Gemini's list-based message content, preventing `AttributeError`.
  - **Config Access**: Updated session validation to use `langgraph.config.get_config()` for reliable `thread_id` and `session_token` access.
  - **Rate Limit Management**: Implemented strategic `time.sleep()` delays in the test suite to respect Gemini's free tier quotas (20 RPM).

